<TITLE> UN urged to form regional river commission </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 16 (bdnews24.com)A Bangladeshi organisation, International Farakka Committee, demanded suspension of 'construction of Tipaimukh barrage' and rightful share of the Indian river Ganges. The organisation called upon the United Nations to form a regional river commission involving China, Nepal, Bhutan and Bangladesh. The leaders of the committee made the demands at a grand rally at Charabari of Tangail Sadar Upazila marking the 33rd anniversary of the historic Farakka Long March led by leader of the oppressed, Moulana Abdul Hamid Khan Bhasani. Former vice-chancellor of Jahangirnagar University professor Jashim Uddin presided over the rally organised on the dried-up river Doleshwari. The former UN water expert Dr SI Khan, Dr.Syed Shafiullah and poet Bulbul Khan Mahmud among others also spoke. A 19-point charter titled 'save river , save country and save Bangladesh' was read out at the rally. 
